    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "To give you more context @Haroenv:\r\n - isRefined used first helps the user not loosing facet values that were selected but are not very important for the current search context\r\n - we went along on all connectors that were proposing sortBy\r\n - forgot to proceed on widgets\r\n - and this change also brings the default scheme meaningful for the type of widget: hierarchical need and menu need name first because they are for navigation (few items). Refinement list is for drilling in the data (more facets)",
